cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE

The paper proposes a novel transfer learning method for visual tasks, which involves generating an intermediate domain that shares similar distribution with the target domain. The method is based on a new concept called manifold criterion, which measures the distribution matching across domains. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of maximum mean discrepancy (MMD) as a domain discrepancy metric, which is related to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the proposed method involves generative models, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
